author: William J. Gedney
notes: Gedney, William J. and Thomas John Hudak, ed. 1993. William J. Gedney's the Saek Language: Glossary, Texts, and Translations. Center for South and Southeast Asian Studies, University of Michigan.The Saek tones are:1  = /34/ mid level, slight rise at the end2  = /11/ low level3  = /31/ falling to low, with glottal constriction4  = /454/ high rising-falling5  = /52/ high falling6  = /32/ mid level, with slight fall and glottal constriction
